[IRON OVERLOAD: BETTER UNDERSTANDING, BETTER CARE].

[Article in French]

Brissot P.

Chronic iron overload, either of genetic (hemochromatoses) or acquired 
(transfusions) origin, leads to frequent disorders, affecting both the quality 
of life and life expectancy. Major recent advances in the knowledge of iron 
metabolism, together with advances in biology, imaging and drug design have 
already significantly improved the diagnostic and therapeutic approaches. These 
conceptual and technological ameliorations should, in the near future, continue 
to benefit the clinical management of iron overloaded patients.

